<br>
If it is based on usage, then the ones who get beat on will hate it.<br>
<br>
If its based on time (Lets take Daoc As example, lose 1 condition every real life day).  That would be better, then you would only have to search for a person to repair your stuff maybe once every 2 weeks.  Items that are stored in the bank will decay at a slower rate (losing 1 condition every 5 days).  That would strengthen the trade economy (cause your stuff rots slower when banked) and the traders will be able to make stuff and repair it.<br>
